ship&#8217;s mission.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Ctrl-F</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'><span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp;&n=
bsp;
</span>Will identify the system the selected ship is in. This should fix a
situation where an explorer is not actually exploring (because the game
doesn&#8217;t think it&#8217;s in a system).<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Alt-Ctrl+ right click</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>: Open a context menu with s=
ome
context specific options. Used for free traders and <span class=3DSpellE>pr=
aites</span>
building at independent worlds.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'><=
o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Fighter/Bomber Hotkeys <=
o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Alt 4</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - designates target. Select target first=
 and
then press Alt 4.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Alt 5</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - Attack order for bombers. After a targ=
et has
been set, select Bomber or Carrier then Alt 5. If bomber is selected orders
THAT bomber to attack, if carrier, all bombers attack target.<o:p></o:p></s=
pan></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Alt 6</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - Attack order for bombers not already
launched, will not alter current attack missions for launched bombers. Alt 4
attack order must be set first.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Alt /</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - Find targeted fighter's parent carrier=
/base.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Alt-a</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - Enable manual fighter ops (so this
carrier&#8217;s bombers won&#8217;t attack unless ordered to). <o:p></o:p><=
/span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'><=
o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Fleet Commands <o:p></o:=
p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;
mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Open the dialog window Ctrl E then enter commands.=
 For
some commands you may need items selected in-game first.<o:p></o:p></span><=
/p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>#disband </span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>- Disband selected fleet <o:p></o:p></spa=
n></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>#disband <span class=3DSpellE>FleetName</=
span></span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - Disband by name of fleet =
inputted
<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>#join <span class=3DSpellE>FleetName</spa=
n></span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - Join fleet by fleet input=
ted <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>#combine <span class=3DSpellE>FleetName</=
span></span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - Join selected fleet to in=
putted
fleet disbanding the selected fleet <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>#combine Fleet1+Fleet2</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - Combine inputted last fle=
et into
inputted first fleet disbanding last fleet <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>#<span class=3DGramE>add</span> [<span
class=3DSpellE>shipDesign</span>]=3D[amount]</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - This command will attempt to reinforce=
 the
currently selected fleet with [amount] of [ship design] ships. If [amount] =
is
left off it defaults to 1. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'><=
o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Misc. Commands<o:p></o:p=
></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;
mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Open the dialog window Ctrl E then enter commands.=
 For
some commands you may need items selected in-game first.<o:p></o:p></span><=
/p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!note </span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>- This adds a reminder note to a ship. It=
 will
trigger a popup with the message when the ship completes its mission.<o:p><=
/o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!note <span class=3DSpellE>nodump</span><=
/span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - Adding <span class=3DSpel=
lE>nodump</span>
to a note makes it so the selected mining ship will not unload its cargo wh=
en
done mining. Good if you want to move the resource to a specific base/plane=
t or
use it to refuel your fleet.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!<span class=3DSpellE>nukem</span></span>=
</b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> &#8211; Destroys all unowne=
d ships.
If passed with true argument <span class=3DGramE>(!<span class=3DSpellE>nuk=
em</span></span>
true) it will keep bases. Use this when starting a story-mode game to get r=
id
of all the graveyards of super ships that many people find unbalancing.<o:p=
></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!clear</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - This will clear the currently selected
ship&#8217;s mission as well as any repeating mission.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!<span class=3DSpellE>braveships</span></=
span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - This changes all ship des=
igns
flee setting from &#8216;enemy encountered&#8217; to &#8216;when
attacked&#8217;<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!<span class=3DSpellE>rangecircles</span>=
</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - This toggles weapon range=
 circles
on and off<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!<span class=3DSpellE>loadtemplates</span=
></span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - Reloads ship templates.<o=
:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DGramE><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:n=
ormal'><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!loan</span></b></span><b
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-=
language:
EN-AU'> [amount]</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN=
-AU'> <span
class=3DGramE>-<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Allows</span>=
 the
player to take out a loan of [amount] credits paid back with interest over a
number of years. <span class=3DGramE>Enter !loan</span> without an amount t=
o see
current loans outstanding.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!stockpile [amount]</span></b><span lang=
=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - Adds [amount] of each strategic resour=
ce to
each empire&#8217;s capital.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!<span class=3DSpellE>stockpilebooty</spa=
n>
[amount</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>] - =
Adds
[amount] of each strategic resource to each pirate empire&#8217;s main base=
.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!spy #</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - Send spy with highest espionage rating=
 on a
steal tech mission (# months).<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!<span class=3DSpellE>freetrader</span></=
span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> &#8211; makes a ship a free=
 trader.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DGramE><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:n=
ormal'><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!infrastructure</span></b></=
span><b
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-=
language:
EN-AU'> [amount]</span></b><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN=
-AU'> <span
class=3DGramE>-<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Adds</span> [=
amount]
money in infrastructure spending to a colony.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!<span class=3DSpellE>godmode</span></spa=
n></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - Toggles total visibility =
of all
ships, bases, and planets on or off.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!overtime [amount]</span></b><span lang=
=3DEN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> &#8211; Adds [amount] years to the start=
 date
for checking victory conditions<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!<span class=3DSpellE>yourock</span></spa=
n></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> - Adds an asteroid orbiting=
 the
selected colony. Cost determined in <span class=3DSpellE>Baconsettings</spa=
n>
file.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span class=3DGramE><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:n=
ormal'><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!<span class=3DSpellE>filter=
resource</span></span></b></span><b
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-=
language:
EN-AU'> [<span class=3DSpellE>resourceID</span>]</span></b><span lang=3DEN-=
AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> <span class=3DGramE>-<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>This</span> will filter the left-h=
and
lists of resource locations and mining stations to only show those with the
selected resource. Input without a <span class=3DSpellE>resourceID</span> to
revert to no filter. These menus will also be sorted by distance from the
currently selected object if there is one.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!price [<span class=3DSpellE>commodityNam=
e</span>]</span></b><span
lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> &#8211; Gives a list of pri=
ces on
the ten closest planets to the currently selected ship.<o:p></o:p></span></=
p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>!science [all]</span></b><span lang=3DEN-=
AU
style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'> &#8211; Turns all explorers into science
ships. Adding the &#8216;all&#8217; parameter does it for all empires. This=
 is
a quick way to make science ships work if you don&#8217;t want to modify all
the design template files manually.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'><=
o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=3D=
EN-AU
style=3D'font-size:11.0pt;mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>Alt + Ctrl + Right Click=
 menu<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-AU style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-AU'>N=
ote: you
MUST hold ALT first and then add CTRL and then Right click. Not doing so wi=
ll
bring up DWU&#8217;s CTRL + right click menu.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

</div>

</body>

